title: Sling Blade
overview: Karl Childers, a simple man hospitalized since his childhood murder of his mother and her lover, is released to start a new life in a small town.

title: Forrest Gump
overview: The presidencies of Kennedy and Johnson, the events of Vietnam, Watergate and other historical events unfold through the perspective of an Alabama man with an IQ of 75, whose only desire is to be reunited with his childhood sweetheart.

title: Black
overview: The cathartic tale of a young woman who can't see, hear or talk and the teacher who brings a ray of light into her dark world.

title: Jodaeiye Nader az Simin
overview: A married couple are faced with a difficult decision - to improve the life of their child by moving to another country or to stay in Iran and look after a deteriorating parent who has Alzheimer's disease.

title: Il conformista
overview: A weak-willed Italian man becomes a fascist flunky who goes abroad to arrange the assassination of his old teacher, now a political dissident.

title: American Beauty
overview: A sexually frustrated suburban father has a mid-life crisis after becoming infatuated with his daughter's best friend.

title: Y tu mamá también
overview: In Mexico, two teenage boys and an attractive older woman embark on a road trip and learn a thing or two about life, friendship, sex, and each other.
stars: ['Maribel Verdú', 'Gael García Bernal', 'Daniel Giménez Cacho', 'Ana López Mercado']

title: Kis Uykusu
overview: A hotel owner and landlord in a remote Turkish village deals with conflicts within his family and a tenant behind on his rent.

title: Fight Club
overview: An insomniac office worker and a devil-may-care soapmaker form an underground fight club that evolves into something much, much more.

title: Vivre sa vie: Film en douze tableaux
overview: Twelve episodic tales in the life of a Parisian woman and her slow descent into prostitution.

title: Rain Man
overview: Selfish yuppie Charlie Babbitt's father left a fortune to his savant brother Raymond and a pittance to Charlie; they travel cross-country.

title: On Golden Pond
overview: Norman is a curmudgeon with an estranged relationship with his daughter Chelsea. At Golden Pond, he and his wife nevertheless agree to care for Billy, the son of Chelsea's new boyfriend, and a most unexpected relationship blooms.

title: Auf der anderen Seite
overview: A Turkish man travels to Istanbul to find the daughter of his father's former girlfriend.

title: Brokeback Mountain
overview: The story of a forbidden and secretive relationship between two cowboys, and their lives over the years.

title: Fanny och Alexander
overview: Two young Swedish children experience the many comedies and tragedies of their family, the Ekdahls.

title: Detachment
overview: A substitute teacher who drifts from classroom to classroom finds a connection to the students and teachers during his latest assignment.

title: Soorarai Pottru
overview: Nedumaaran Rajangam "Maara" sets out to make the common man fly and in the process takes on the world's most capital intensive industry and several enemies who stand in his way.

title: Fa yeung nin wah
overview: Two neighbors, a woman and a man, form a strong bond after both suspect extramarital activities of their spouses. However, they agree to keep their bond platonic so as not to commit similar wrongs.
stars: ['Tony Chiu-Wai Leung', 'Maggie Cheung', 'Ping Lam Siu', "Tung Cho 'Joe' Cheung"]

title: Kokuhaku
overview: A psychological thriller of a grieving mother turned cold-blooded avenger with a twisty master plan to pay back those who were responsible for her daughter's death.

title: Die Welle
overview: A high school teacher's experiment to demonstrate to his students what life is like under a dictatorship spins horribly out of control when he forms a social unit with a life of its own.
